76
00:06:56,981 --> 00:07:00,109
That’s right, Steven.
But there's another boy.

77
00:07:00,451 --> 00:07:03,784
- Heh. Another boy?
- Yeah.

78
00:07:06,824 --> 00:07:10,282
Big Mike. Sleeps on my couch
from time to time.

79
00:07:10,461 --> 00:07:13,021
It's a bad deal. You know,
his mom's on that crack pipe.

80
00:07:13,197 --> 00:07:16,655
He ain't got nobody else. He just
wanted to come along for the ride.

81
00:07:17,034 --> 00:07:18,695
- They're here?
- Yeah.

82
00:07:19,737 --> 00:07:23,173
Now, the little one, that’s Steven...

83
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:24,932
...and the big one...

84
00:07:25,109 --> 00:07:26,201
Big Mike.

85
00:07:35,252 --> 00:07:36,844
Swish!

86
00:07:39,356 --> 00:07:41,381
Big Mike! Ha-ha.

87
00:07:43,193 --> 00:07:44,626
Come on.

88
00:07:51,502 --> 00:07:53,094
Mother of God.

89
00:07:54,571 --> 00:07:57,540
<i>Steven Hamilton's paperwork
looks acceptable to me...</i>

90
00:07:57,708 --> 00:08:00,939
...and I believe he'll do fine.
But this other kid...

91
00:08:01,111 --> 00:08:03,170
- Big Mike.
- Michael Oher...

92
00:08:03,347 --> 00:08:05,781
...gives us no reason to believe that...

93
00:08:05,949 --> 00:08:09,316
...based on his records,
that he would be successful here.

94
00:08:09,486 --> 00:08:10,680
Well, how bad could it be?

95
00:08:10,854 --> 00:08:14,381
We're not exactly sure how old he is,
due to his lack of records.

96
00:08:14,558 --> 00:08:17,550
He has a measured IQ of 80,
which is sixth percentile.

97
00:08:18,128 --> 00:08:22,394
His grade-point average
begins with zero, 0.6.

98
00:08:22,566 --> 00:08:24,500
Everyone passed him along.

99
00:08:24,668 --> 00:08:28,104
They gave him D's so they could
hand their problem off to the next school.

100
00:08:30,074 --> 00:08:31,405
He's a brave kid.

101
00:08:34,178 --> 00:08:38,706
For wanting to come here,
for wanting a quality education.

102
00:08:38,882 --> 00:08:43,376
An education denied him by
the poor quality of schools he's attended.

103
00:08:43,554 --> 00:08:47,354
Most kids with his background wouldn’t
come within 200 miles of this place.

104
00:08:47,524 --> 00:08:52,484
Coach Cotton, we understand your interest
in this young man’s athletic abilities.

105
00:08:52,663 --> 00:08:55,632
He wouldn’t be able to play sports
until he got his grades up.

106
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:57,892
Forget sports.

107
00:08:58,102 --> 00:08:59,592
Look at the wall.

108
00:08:59,770 --> 00:09:03,968
"Christian." We either take that
seriously or we paint over it.

109
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:08,276
You don't admit Michael Oher
because of sports.

110
00:09:08,445 --> 00:09:11,505
You admit him because
it's the right thing to do.

111
00:09:56,994 --> 00:09:58,655
Class, this is Mike Oher...

112
00:09:58,829 --> 00:10:02,458
...and he's new here so I expect
you all to make him feel welcome.

113
00:10:02,633 --> 00:10:04,828
Mike, just take any empty seat.

114
00:10:08,338 --> 00:10:11,398
This is a quiz based on the information...

115
00:10:11,575 --> 00:10:15,067
...you learned last year
in your science curriculum.

116
00:10:15,245 --> 00:10:18,009
Don't worry, it's not gonna be graded.

117
00:10:18,182 --> 00:10:20,912
I just wanna see how much information
we need to hit again.

118
00:10:21,084 --> 00:10:23,416
Just answer whatever you know.

119
00:10:55,786 --> 00:10:58,050
Thank you.

120
00:11:14,638 --> 00:11:18,199
- Can I leave now?
- Yeah.

121
00:11:22,179 --> 00:11:23,441
Take your book.

122
00:11:41,899 --> 00:11:43,992
I'm tired
of having someone always in our home.

123
00:11:44,167 --> 00:11:45,930
I'm tired of him eating all the food.

124
00:11:46,103 --> 00:11:48,537
Look, man, you gotta be Christian
about this thing.

125
00:11:48,705 --> 00:11:50,900
Let somebody else
be Christian about this thing.

126
00:11:51,074 --> 00:11:54,271
Dee, come on, I can’t kick him out
on the street like he's some dog.

127
00:11:54,444 --> 00:11:56,344
Let somebody else
take the responsibility.

128
00:11:56,513 --> 00:11:59,141
What, you want me to go to
Beale Street and drop him off?

129
00:11:59,316 --> 00:12:01,307
When do I have time
just to be with you?

130
00:12:01,485 --> 00:12:06,218
All right, all right. Whatever.
You win. I'll take care of it.

131
00:12:10,727 --> 00:12:13,161
I don't care if Patrick Ramsey
approved the chair.

132
00:12:13,330 --> 00:12:16,766
He's an NFL quarterback,
not Martha fricking Stewart.

133
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:21,097
Because there is a difference
between Bunny Williams and a La-Z-Boy.

134
00:12:21,271 --> 00:12:23,762
<i>No, see, when MTV Cribs
comes to his house...</i>

135
00:12:23,941 --> 00:12:25,806
...he’ll be showing off
his home theater.

136
00:12:25,976 --> 00:12:28,501
All I'm gonna see
is a brown Barcalounger.

137
00:12:28,679 --> 00:12:31,307
No, listen to me, I'm the designer,
my name is on it.

138
00:12:31,481 --> 00:12:34,678
Deliver what I ordered, all right?
Thank you.

139
00:12:43,994 --> 00:12:45,052
Yeah!

140
00:12:48,432 --> 00:12:51,026
What’d I miss?
- Collins just got a dig.

141
00:12:51,201 --> 00:12:53,829
It's girls' volleyball, Mom.
You didn't miss anything.

142
00:12:56,740 --> 00:12:57,866
Oh!

143
00:12:58,041 --> 00:13:00,976
- Come on, Collins, move your feet.
Good job, Collins.

144
00:13:01,144 --> 00:13:02,236
Go.

145
00:13:06,283 --> 00:13:07,545
We'll wait for you outside.

146
00:13:07,718 --> 00:13:10,278
Don't double condition in
the shower, you have homework.

147
00:13:10,454 --> 00:13:11,921
I'm going to Cannon’s to study.

148
00:13:12,089 --> 00:13:17,550
SJ! SJ, do not go in the girls' locker
room again. Come here! SJ, come here!

149
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:33,275
<i>The big kid's been here
for, what, a month?</i>

150
00:13:33,677 --> 00:13:35,577
He's still not cutting it in my class.

151
00:13:35,746 --> 00:13:39,443
Why does Admissions do this?
I mean, it's not fair to us or the boy.

152
00:13:39,616 --> 00:13:41,277
They're just setting him up to fail.

153
00:13:41,451 --> 00:13:43,783
I don't think he has any idea
of what I'm teaching.

154
00:13:43,954 --> 00:13:46,445
And how would you know if he did?
He won't even talk.

155
00:13:47,424 --> 00:13:48,448
He writes.

156
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:50,525
His name. Barely.

157
00:13:51,695 --> 00:13:54,255
He threw this in the trash can.

158
00:13:57,968 --> 00:14:00,801
"I look and I see white everywhere:

159
00:14:00,971 --> 00:14:06,136
White walls, white floors,
and a lot of white people.

160
00:14:06,476 --> 00:14:11,743
The teachers do not know I have no idea
of anything they are talking about.

161
00:14:11,915 --> 00:14:14,975
I do not wanna listen to anyone,
especially the teachers.

162
00:14:15,152 --> 00:14:20,112
They are giving homework and expecting
me to do the problems on my own.

163
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:22,890
I have never done homework in my life.

164
00:14:23,693 --> 00:14:28,460
I go to the bathroom,
look in the mirror and say:

165
00:14:28,765 --> 00:14:30,460
"This is not Michael Oher."

166
00:14:35,338 --> 00:14:37,431
He entitled it "White Walls."

167
00:14:37,707 --> 00:14:39,572
How's the spelling?

168
00:14:51,488 --> 00:14:52,955
Hi.

169
00:15:00,363 --> 00:15:03,924
Smile at them.
It lets them know you're their friend.

170
00:15:08,872 --> 00:15:10,567
You're Big Mike, right?

171
00:15:11,808 --> 00:15:12,968
Well, I'm Sean.

172
00:15:13,143 --> 00:15:17,944
But everyone calls me SJ. It's for
Sean Junior. My father's name is Sean.

173
00:15:18,115 --> 00:15:22,017
Sean Tuohy? He was a basketball star
at Ole Miss, point guard.

174
00:15:22,185 --> 00:15:24,119
Now he owns like a million Taco Bells.

175
00:15:34,731 --> 00:15:36,562
Who is that, SJ?
Big Mike.

176
00:15:38,468 --> 00:15:40,561
Get your feet off my dash.

177
00:15:41,638 --> 00:15:43,037
Thank you. Put on your seat belt.

178
00:15:51,982 --> 00:15:53,677
Big Mike?

179
00:15:56,553 --> 00:16:00,751
Mike, I got a call from someone
at the police department.

180
00:16:04,628 --> 00:16:10,692
You remember a story in the papers
a while back about a man who...

181
00:16:10,901 --> 00:16:13,335
...fell off an overpass?

182
00:16:13,503 --> 00:16:15,698
No one knew who he was.

183
00:16:15,872 --> 00:16:20,673
They didn't know if he jumped or if...

184
00:16:21,711 --> 00:16:25,909
Well, anyway, he- He passed away.

185
00:16:29,252 --> 00:16:31,982
Mike, that man was your father.

186
00:16:35,258 --> 00:16:38,159
They've been looking for
somebody to notify and they-

187
00:16:38,328 --> 00:16:41,456
They found your name in our registry.

188
00:16:43,366 --> 00:16:45,926
I'm really sorry, son.

189
00:16:51,041 --> 00:16:53,032
Were you close to him?

190
00:16:57,414 --> 00:17:00,076
When's the last time you saw him?

191
00:17:05,255 --> 00:17:07,314
I don't know.

192
00:18:39,983 --> 00:18:42,713
- He knows it!
- Who knows it and what does he know?

193
00:18:42,986 --> 00:18:46,513
The material. Michael Oher.
I gave him this test verbally.

194
00:18:46,690 --> 00:18:50,057
- Is that even allowed?
- A "C"? On how big a curve?

195
00:18:50,226 --> 00:18:53,127
He's been listening all along.
It's amazing what he's absorbed.

196
00:18:53,296 --> 00:18:57,357
And, trust me, he's listening to you too.
Now, his reading level is low...

197
00:18:57,534 --> 00:19:01,026
...and he's got no idea
how to learn in a classroom...

198
00:19:01,204 --> 00:19:06,107
I'm not saying he's gonna pass,
but Big Mike is not stupid.

199
00:19:06,276 --> 00:19:08,574
Hey. Good job.
Mama. Daddy.

200
00:19:08,745 --> 00:19:10,762
Good job.
Hey I got a question for you.

201
00:19:10,812 --> 00:19:11,403
Yeah?

202
00:19:11,581 --> 00:19:15,312
There was a little girl about two rows
back. What was her name?

203
00:19:15,485 --> 00:19:17,680
- Oh, that was Kinsey.
- Kinsey, yeah.

204
00:19:17,854 --> 00:19:20,322
I saw your little Indian feathers
get all ruffled up.

205
00:19:20,490 --> 00:19:21,684
Yeah! She is nice.

206
00:19:21,858 --> 00:19:23,826
SJ. Don't let this go to your head...

207
00:19:23,993 --> 00:19:26,791
...but I thought you were
very convincing in the role of...

208
00:19:26,963 --> 00:19:28,794
- Indian Number 3?
- Yes.

209
00:19:28,965 --> 00:19:32,366
I tried out for the chief,
but they gave it to Andy Sung.

210
00:19:32,535 --> 00:19:36,596
I can’t be sure, but I think there's
some multi-cultural-bias thing working.

211
00:19:36,773 --> 00:19:39,469
Or maybe they just thought
that he'd make a better chief.

212
00:19:39,642 --> 00:19:41,439
Dad, he's, like, Chinese.

213
00:19:41,611 --> 00:19:43,010
Yeah, and you're Irish.

214
00:19:43,179 --> 00:19:45,739
If you weren't the chief,
how did you get the headdress?

215
00:19:45,915 --> 00:19:49,146
Dad, I'm gonna need a few more
of those free quesadilla tickets.

216
00:19:51,621 --> 00:19:53,851
And where does the acorn fall?

217
00:19:54,023 --> 00:19:57,015
Hey, don't laugh too hard.
The quesadillas saved our ass.

218
00:19:57,193 --> 00:19:58,785
Don't use the A-word.

219
00:20:04,734 --> 00:20:05,996
What is he wearing?

220
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:09,435
It's freezing.

221
00:20:09,606 --> 00:20:12,040
- What's his name again?
- Big Mike.

222
00:20:12,942 --> 00:20:15,172
Where is he going?

223
00:20:16,279 --> 00:20:19,407
Hey, Big Mike. Where you headed?

224
00:20:19,582 --> 00:20:20,606
Gym.

225
00:20:21,384 --> 00:20:22,408
Go ahead.

226
00:20:34,597 --> 00:20:35,689
Turn around.

227
00:20:43,273 --> 00:20:44,467
Big Mike!

228
00:20:44,641 --> 00:20:46,506
Stop the car.

229
00:20:50,447 --> 00:20:51,539
Big Mike.

230
00:20:52,449 --> 00:20:55,009
Hey. My name's Leigh Anne Tuohy.
My kids go to Wingate.

231
00:20:55,185 --> 00:20:56,812
You said you were going to the gym?

232
