472
00:40:33,695 --> 00:40:37,153
I talked to Coach Cotton. He said
Michael’s grades have improved enough...

473
00:40:37,332 --> 00:40:40,165
...that he can go out
for spring football in March.

474
00:40:40,335 --> 00:40:43,702
- Isn't that great?
- Oh, man! You're gonna crush some people!

475
00:40:51,046 --> 00:40:53,844
- Hey, guys, how we doing?
- Great, thank you.

476
00:40:54,716 --> 00:40:58,174
I've got a design book I need to get.
Why don't you check our reservation?

477
00:40:58,353 --> 00:41:00,253
They'll seat us right away.
Can't it wait?

478
00:41:00,422 --> 00:41:02,890
They might be closed by then.
Come on, SJ!

479
00:41:03,058 --> 00:41:04,582
I need some new magazines.

480
00:41:06,962 --> 00:41:08,862
Michael, come on. Come on.

481
00:41:20,008 --> 00:41:23,341
Collins? Collins?

482
00:41:23,812 --> 00:41:26,337
Collins, come on, your dad's
already PO'd. Let's go.

483
00:41:26,515 --> 00:41:27,709
Over here.

484
00:41:36,091 --> 00:41:40,790
You remember this one, Mom?
You read it to us like a thousand times.

485
00:41:41,196 --> 00:41:44,893
"He gnashed his terrible teeth
and he roared his terrible roar."

486
00:41:45,967 --> 00:41:47,867
I always liked this one.

487
00:41:48,036 --> 00:41:49,401
<i>Mm. Ferdinand.</i>

488
00:41:49,705 --> 00:41:51,536
Me too.

489
00:41:51,740 --> 00:41:55,232
Michael, your mama ever read
either one of those books to you?

490
00:41:58,480 --> 00:42:00,038
No?

491
00:42:00,749 --> 00:42:02,307
How cute!

492
00:42:02,484 --> 00:42:03,974
It was a good steak, huh?

493
00:42:04,152 --> 00:42:05,141
Thank you, Daddy.

494
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:06,878
Thank you for a lovely dinner, Papa.

495
00:42:07,055 --> 00:42:08,420
Here we go.

496
00:42:43,625 --> 00:42:48,358
Michael. Who was that boy
you were talking to at the restaurant?

497
00:42:48,530 --> 00:42:50,498
Marcus.

498
00:42:51,166 --> 00:42:55,262
- Marcus, and he- He works there?
- Yeah.

499
00:42:56,371 --> 00:42:58,202
How do you know him?

500
00:42:59,741 --> 00:43:01,936
He's my brother.

501
00:43:08,483 --> 00:43:11,384
Well, we'd really- We'd really
like to meet him someday.

502
00:43:12,621 --> 00:43:14,919
Would that be okay with you?

503
00:43:15,390 --> 00:43:17,324
I don't know where he stays.

504
00:43:18,026 --> 00:43:20,517
When was the last time you saw him?

505
00:43:23,365 --> 00:43:24,923
When I was little, maybe.

506
00:43:29,571 --> 00:43:33,632
<i>"Once upon a time in Spain,
there was a little bull...</i>

507
00:43:33,809 --> 00:43:36,972
...and his name was Ferdinand.

508
00:43:37,345 --> 00:43:40,644
All the other little bulls he lived with
would run and jump...

509
00:43:40,816 --> 00:43:43,546
...and butt their heads together.

510
00:43:44,186 --> 00:43:46,711
But not Ferdinand.

511
00:43:47,889 --> 00:43:53,691
He liked to sit just quietly
and smell the flowers.

512
00:43:54,796 --> 00:43:58,596
He had a favorite spot out
in the pasture under a cork tree.

513
00:44:00,202 --> 00:44:02,329
<i>It was his favorite tree...</i>

514
00:44:02,504 --> 00:44:08,067
<i>...and he would sit in its shade
all day and smell the flowers. "</i>

515
00:44:08,243 --> 00:44:11,007
- Good night.
- Good night.

516
00:44:13,381 --> 00:44:15,975
- What?
- What?

517
00:44:16,251 --> 00:44:18,378
Why are you smiling?

518
00:44:18,653 --> 00:44:23,022
I don't know, I'm just happy.
Real happy.

519
00:44:23,191 --> 00:44:26,160
Does this happiness have anything
to do with Michael?

520
00:44:26,328 --> 00:44:27,955
No.

521
00:44:28,763 --> 00:44:31,664
It has everything to do with Michael.

522
00:44:33,034 --> 00:44:35,525
Mm. Mm.

523
00:44:35,770 --> 00:44:37,738
- Happy's good.
- Mm.

524
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:40,367
You know what I think we should do?

525
00:44:40,542 --> 00:44:43,340
We should start a charity
for kids like Michael.

526
00:44:43,511 --> 00:44:45,945
- Okay.
- Maybe fund a program at Wingate.

527
00:44:46,114 --> 00:44:47,138
Sure.

528
00:44:47,315 --> 00:44:49,579
Lord knows that school
could use a little color.

529
00:44:49,751 --> 00:44:53,346
Poor Michael’s like a fly in the milk
in that place.

530
00:44:53,521 --> 00:44:55,421
Are you listening to me?

531
00:44:57,259 --> 00:45:01,889
- Hmm?
- I try to concentrate on one...

532
00:45:02,697 --> 00:45:04,358
...thing...

533
00:45:04,799 --> 00:45:06,460
...at a time.

534
00:45:06,635 --> 00:45:08,330
You knew I was a multitasker...

535
00:45:08,503 --> 00:45:09,868
...when you married me, right?

536
00:45:10,038 --> 00:45:14,099
- I sure did.
- Right. Okay, just checking.

537
00:45:17,913 --> 00:45:22,282
Okay, Tuohy family.
Big smiles, everyone.

538
00:45:23,084 --> 00:45:26,986
And one, two, three!

539
00:45:29,424 --> 00:45:30,448
Michael.

540
00:45:30,625 --> 00:45:32,752
Come on down here
and get in the next one.

541
00:45:32,961 --> 00:45:35,953
Come on. Come on. Come on down.

542
00:45:41,303 --> 00:45:44,363
Oh, come on. It's not like I'm gonna
put it on the Christmas card.

543
00:45:44,539 --> 00:45:48,839
Okay, let's scootch in a little tighter.

544
00:45:49,010 --> 00:45:50,534
That's good.

545
00:45:51,313 --> 00:45:52,644
Really big smiles.

546
00:45:52,814 --> 00:45:55,476
Okay, one, two, three.

547
00:45:55,650 --> 00:45:57,447
- Say "Rebels!"
Rebels!

548
00:46:01,656 --> 00:46:04,181
<i>- a blitz off
the corner, quick pass over the middle.</i>

549
00:46:04,359 --> 00:46:08,625
<i>- The hot route was there. And that's...
I got it.</i>

550
00:46:09,297 --> 00:46:11,629
- Who's winning?
- Tennessee.

551
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:14,462
- Ugh. Who they playing?
- Clemson.

552
00:46:14,636 --> 00:46:17,298
Your mama roots against Tennessee
no matter who they play?

553
00:46:17,472 --> 00:46:19,906
Uh- Yes, I do. With gusto.

554
00:46:20,075 --> 00:46:21,975
She can’t stand Tennessee.

555
00:46:22,143 --> 00:46:25,203
Collie-bell, I thought you were
going over to your boyfriend's.

556
00:46:25,380 --> 00:46:27,245
Thought I'd hang around here
for the day.

557
00:46:28,116 --> 00:46:29,549
Hmm.

558
00:46:29,784 --> 00:46:31,342
I like that.

559
00:46:31,519 --> 00:46:34,420
There's a couple messages on the machine.
I didn't check them.

560
00:46:34,589 --> 00:46:36,022
All right.

561
00:46:36,992 --> 00:46:40,393
<i>Hey, Sean, hey, Leigh Anne, it's
your cousin Bobby. Happy New Year's.</i>

562
00:46:40,628 --> 00:46:43,495
- Listen, I've had about five cold ones...
- Of course you have.

563
00:46:43,665 --> 00:46:45,724
<i>...so I'm just gonna go ahead and ask:</i>

564
00:46:46,301 --> 00:46:49,634
Did y’all know there's a colored boy
in your Christmas card?

565
00:46:52,674 --> 00:46:54,403
What?

566
00:46:55,010 --> 00:46:58,002
You just looked teeny-tiny next to him.

567
00:46:58,179 --> 00:47:00,147
Right? Like Jessica Lange and King Kong.

568
00:47:01,549 --> 00:47:04,143
Hey, does Michael get
the family discount at Taco Bell?

569
00:47:04,319 --> 00:47:07,846
Because if he does,
Sean's gonna lose a few stores.

570
00:47:08,023 --> 00:47:09,081
He's a good kid.

571
00:47:09,257 --> 00:47:12,192
Well, I say you make it official
and just adopt him.

572
00:47:13,962 --> 00:47:18,262
He's gonna be 18 in a few months. Doesn't
really make much sense to legally adopt.

573
00:47:21,436 --> 00:47:22,460
Leigh Anne.

574
00:47:22,937 --> 00:47:25,462
Is this some sort of white-guilt thing?

575
00:47:25,807 --> 00:47:28,105
What will your daddy say?

576
00:47:28,810 --> 00:47:32,109
Um... Before or after
he turns over in his grave?

577
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:34,748
Daddy's been gone five years, Elaine.

578
00:47:34,916 --> 00:47:38,044
Make matters worse, you were
at the funeral. Remember?

579
00:47:38,219 --> 00:47:40,585
You wore Chanel
and that awful black hat.

580
00:47:40,755 --> 00:47:42,552
Look, here's the deal.

581
00:47:42,724 --> 00:47:45,955
I don't need y’all to approve
my choices, all right?

582
00:47:46,127 --> 00:47:50,291
But I do ask that you respect them. You
have no idea what this boy's been through.

583
00:47:50,465 --> 00:47:53,127
And if this is gonna become
some running diatribe...

584
00:47:53,301 --> 00:47:55,997
...I can find an overpriced salad
a lot closer to home.

585
00:47:58,006 --> 00:48:01,373
- Leigh Anne, I'm sorry. We didn't intend to-
- No, we didn't, really.

586
00:48:01,543 --> 00:48:04,774
I think what you're doing is so great.

587
00:48:04,946 --> 00:48:07,710
To open up your home to him?

588
00:48:08,083 --> 00:48:10,347
Honey, you're changing that boy's life.

589
00:48:11,186 --> 00:48:12,778
No.

590
00:48:13,321 --> 00:48:14,913
He's changing mine.

591
00:48:16,491 --> 00:48:18,823
And that’s awesome for you,
but what about Collins?

592
00:48:20,662 --> 00:48:22,960
- What about Collins?
Aren't you worried?

593
00:48:23,131 --> 00:48:24,826
I mean, even just a little?

594
00:48:24,999 --> 00:48:29,436
He's a boy, a large, black boy,
sleeping under the same roof.

595
00:48:32,140 --> 00:48:33,437
Shame on you.

596
00:48:38,646 --> 00:48:39,977
I've got this.

597
00:48:42,083 --> 00:48:43,880
<i>Be honest with me, okay?</i>

598
00:48:45,787 --> 00:48:49,450
Does Michael being here
make you uncomfortable?

599
00:48:50,091 --> 00:48:53,527
They're stupid kids.
Who cares what they say?

600
00:48:53,695 --> 00:48:56,858
- What kids?
- At school.

601
00:48:57,365 --> 00:48:58,696
They're juvenile.

602
00:48:58,867 --> 00:49:00,892
And what do the juvenile kids say?

603
00:49:01,970 --> 00:49:04,200
It's really not worth repeating.

604
00:49:05,340 --> 00:49:07,240
And don't worry about SJ.

605
00:49:07,542 --> 00:49:11,740
He likes all the attention. He introduces
Michael as his big brother.

606
00:49:16,451 --> 00:49:17,816
And what about you?

607
00:49:18,219 --> 00:49:20,187
It's fine.

608
00:49:21,990 --> 00:49:25,084
I mean, you can’t just throw him
out on the street.

609
00:49:25,260 --> 00:49:27,421
I could make other arrangements.

610
00:49:31,432 --> 00:49:33,992
Hi, Mike.
- Hi. Need a push?

611
00:49:34,169 --> 00:49:35,796
Yes.

612
00:49:40,875 --> 00:49:43,400
Oh.
Higher, Mike, higher!

613
00:49:47,215 --> 00:49:49,206
Higher!

614
00:49:53,421 --> 00:49:55,582
Higher!

615
00:49:59,260 --> 00:50:02,388
Don't look down, don't look down. Ah!

616
00:50:35,630 --> 00:50:38,599
- Where are you going?
- Collins?

617
00:50:50,211 --> 00:50:52,509
Quit looking at me like that.

618
00:50:52,680 --> 00:50:55,615
I mean, we study together at home.

619
00:51:12,333 --> 00:51:16,793
You know how much those things weigh?
This kid's gonna make us all famous.

620
00:51:18,506 --> 00:51:22,738
Easy, Bert, man. It's only the spring.
He hasn't even had his first practice yet.

621
00:51:22,910 --> 00:51:24,935
No, he's a player.

622
00:51:25,380 --> 00:51:26,870
Break!

623
00:51:27,348 --> 00:51:29,316
Ready.
Break!

624
00:51:29,917 --> 00:51:33,580
Get down, son.
Get down in your stance. In your stance!

625
00:51:33,855 --> 00:51:34,879
Go!

626
00:51:36,090 --> 00:51:39,856
Shuck him, shuck him! Ah, ah-

627
00:51:40,928 --> 00:51:44,022
Mike, son, you-
You fought off the block...

628
00:51:44,198 --> 00:51:46,530
...but then you wanna shuck
the blocker.

629
00:51:46,701 --> 00:51:49,670
All right? Shuck him. All right, let's go.

630
00:51:50,471 --> 00:51:52,200
Huddle up.

631
00:51:52,373 --> 00:51:54,102
Papa.

632
00:51:55,476 --> 00:51:56,875
How's he doing?

633
00:51:57,045 --> 00:51:58,569
Hasn't quite gotten the hang of it yet.

634
00:52:06,721 --> 00:52:07,813
Mike, son.

635
00:52:07,989 --> 00:52:10,082
Shuck the blocker, don't tote him!

636
00:52:10,258 --> 00:52:12,192
Set, go!

637
00:52:13,594 --> 00:52:17,223
No, no, no! No, no, no!

638
00:52:17,965 --> 00:52:19,523
Set, go!

639
00:52:28,242 --> 00:52:30,039
Balloons! They're balloons!

640
00:52:30,678 --> 00:52:33,613
Guys, quit looking at the balloons.
Everybody!

641
00:52:33,781 --> 00:52:36,648
Most kids from bad situations
can’t wait to be violent...

642
00:52:36,818 --> 00:52:38,445
...and that comes out on the field.

643
00:52:38,619 --> 00:52:41,782
But this kid, he acts like
he doesn't wanna hit anyone.

644
00:52:41,956 --> 00:52:43,856
He's Ferdinand the Bull.

645
00:52:44,025 --> 00:52:45,754
What?
- Nothing.

646
00:52:47,261 --> 00:52:51,823
I thought he was gonna be a player. I can’t
believe I used up all my chips to get him in.

647
00:52:51,999 --> 00:52:54,160
I thought you said
it was your Christian duty.

648
00:52:55,870 --> 00:52:58,566
Look, Bert, he's never even played before.

649
00:52:59,640 --> 00:53:02,939
Yeah, and he won't this fall if he
doesn't improve a lot before then.

650
00:53:03,277 --> 00:53:05,142
Who died and made him Bear Bryant?

651
00:53:06,848 --> 00:53:08,213
Unbelievable.

652
00:53:09,350 --> 00:53:11,477
Oh, God bless me.

653
00:53:11,652 --> 00:53:13,313
This is your summer workout sheet.

654
00:53:13,488 --> 00:53:15,718
Now, first it says to warm up
and get loose.

655
00:53:16,657 --> 00:53:18,420
Well, go ahead, get loose.

656
00:53:21,295 --> 00:53:22,853
Are you loose?

657
00:53:23,231 --> 00:53:26,997
Okay. Next, it's five 100-yard runs
to stretch out your legs.

658
00:53:27,168 --> 00:53:29,432
- Can we just go home and play video games?
- Look!

659
00:53:29,604 --> 00:53:32,767
Everybody at Wingate is expecting you
to be a star football player.

660
00:53:32,940 --> 00:53:34,567
Don't wanna let them down,
do you?

661
00:53:34,742 --> 00:53:36,676
- I don't know.
- What about Dad and Mom?

662
00:53:36,844 --> 00:53:39,506
Because, you see, in our family,
everyone's an athlete.

663
00:53:39,680 --> 00:53:43,741
Dad was a basketball star.
Collins plays volleyball and runs track.

664
00:53:43,918 --> 00:53:46,250
And me, well, as you know, I do it all.

665
00:53:46,421 --> 00:53:48,912
And Mom- Well, Mom was a cheerleader...

666
00:53:49,090 --> 00:53:52,821
...which doesn't exactly count,
but don't tell her I said that. Okay?

667
00:53:52,994 --> 00:53:55,155
- Okay.
- Okay.

668
00:53:56,764 --> 00:53:59,824
- Yeah. Fifty.
Uhn.

669
00:54:00,001 --> 00:54:01,935
Fifty-one.

670
00:54:02,270 --> 00:54:05,603
Fifty-two. Fifty-three.

671
00:54:05,807 --> 00:54:08,970
Come on, you can get him.
Go, go, go! Come on!

672
00:54:09,143 --> 00:54:10,633
Five seconds left in the game!

673
00:54:12,513 --> 00:54:13,980
This way!

674
00:54:14,148 --> 00:54:15,308
This way!

675
00:54:15,483 --> 00:54:19,920
High knees, high knees, high knees!
Speed kills, baby! Run like the wind!

676
00:54:21,289 --> 00:54:22,916
Go, Michael, go!

677
00:54:23,124 --> 00:54:24,955
Ninety-eight.

678
00:54:25,359 --> 00:54:26,383
Ninety-nine.

679
00:54:28,229 --> 00:54:29,526
One hundred.

680
00:54:29,697 --> 00:54:32,393
Move your feet, move your feet!
Come on, come on! Go!

681
00:54:32,567 --> 00:54:33,898
- There you go.
- Ahh!

682
00:54:34,068 --> 00:54:36,468
You gotta get the tackle,
come on, come on, come on!

683
00:54:37,205 --> 00:54:38,467
Come on, Michael.

684
00:55:03,097 --> 00:55:04,121
Mrs. Tuohy?

685
00:55:04,298 --> 00:55:07,734
I hear "Mrs. Tuohy," I look over
my shoulder for my mother-in-law.

686
00:55:07,902 --> 00:55:11,030
Call me Leigh Anne or Mama
or almost anything else.

687
00:55:14,175 --> 00:55:17,167
- Can you help me get something?
- What?

688
00:55:19,614 --> 00:55:20,842
Driver's license.

689
00:55:22,750 --> 00:55:26,083
Why do you need a driver's license
when you don't even have a car?

690
00:55:33,528 --> 00:55:36,053
Michael, why do you want
a driver's license?

691
00:55:36,764 --> 00:55:39,631
It's something to carry
with my name on it.

692
00:55:46,874 --> 00:55:49,399
There's no one by the name of
Michael Oher in the system.

693
00:55:49,577 --> 00:55:51,977
Another last name, perhaps?

694
00:55:54,215 --> 00:55:56,911
Look, I will sign something
that says he lives with us.

695
00:55:57,084 --> 00:56:00,144
We'll pay for all of the insurance.
Whatever it takes. Okay?

696
00:56:01,122 --> 00:56:02,316
What's it gonna take?

697
00:56:02,490 --> 00:56:05,220
You wanna do what?
- You heard me.

698
00:56:05,393 --> 00:56:08,658
- Shouldn’t we at least talk about this?
- What do you think we're doing?

699
00:56:08,829 --> 00:56:10,922
And don't act like
I'm going behind your back.

700
00:56:11,098 --> 00:56:14,625
I know you put us down as
Michael’s medical contact at school.

701
00:56:14,802 --> 00:56:17,737
There is a huge difference
between paying for a broken arm...

702
00:56:17,905 --> 00:56:21,602
...and being legally responsible for
someone. I mean, a kid we barely know.

703
00:56:21,776 --> 00:56:25,075
That's another thing. We need to
find out more about his past.

704
00:56:25,246 --> 00:56:29,307
He won't talk about it. He's like an onion.
You have to peel him back a layer at a time.

705
00:56:29,483 --> 00:56:31,747
Not if you use a knife.

706
00:56:32,453 --> 00:56:35,616
What if we took him to a child
psychologist or something?

707
00:56:35,790 --> 00:56:38,452
- Do you really expect Big Mike to-?
- Michael.

708
00:56:38,626 --> 00:56:40,560
Do you expect Michael
to lie on a couch...

709
00:56:40,728 --> 00:56:43,253
...and talk about his childhood
like he's Woody Allen?

710
00:56:43,431 --> 00:56:46,093
I mean, Michael’s gift
is his ability to forget.

711
00:56:46,267 --> 00:56:50,226
He's mad at no one and he really
doesn't care what happened in the past.

712
00:56:50,871 --> 00:56:51,997
You're right.

713
00:56:52,707 --> 00:56:55,972
Excuse me? "You're right"?

714
00:56:56,143 --> 00:56:58,611
How'd those words taste
coming out of your mouth?

715
00:56:58,779 --> 00:57:00,212
Like vinegar.

